    <li><?php echo erTranslationClassLhTranslation::getInstance()->getTranslation('genericbot/helpattributes', 'Consecutive visitor messages do not change owner by themselves. While owner stays the same, each eligible visitor-side gap can keep increasing that owner\'s duration.');?></li>
    <li><?php echo erTranslationClassLhTranslation::getInstance()->getTranslation('genericbot/helpattributes', 'For response metrics tied to participants (FRT/AART/MART), consecutive visitor messages also do not reset pending visitor start marker. Start remains first pending point until valid operator reply.');?></li>
    <li><?php echo erTranslationClassLhTranslation::getInstance()->getTranslation('genericbot/helpattributes', 'Accept/transfer/owner-change meta events can switch owner context, but they do not count as visitor replies. They only affect which human owner receives later eligible gaps.');?></li>
    <li><?php echo erTranslationClassLhTranslation::getInstance()->getTranslation('genericbot/helpattributes', 'Bot/auto-responder side is not tracked as a human participant owner, so it does not create a separate human agent duration entry.');?></li>
